snippet.textDisplay: This show has got the same characters who were in it years ago, still sulking about but having gone through every marriage combination possible with each other, and a new generation of characters seemingly named after dead ones but just as grim, talking in drama school "propppaaaa werkin' clarss" accents, being orchestrated by professional cocker-ney Willy The Wonqueror aka Daniel Dyer. I did enjoy the ridiculously constant miserable tone though. But I think really this show would be improved by the existential crisis' of characters and some re-telling of classic literature, Sci-Fi and mythology, such as Ian Beale on a Dante's Inferno style trawl through Walford, Kat Slater as a Prometheus style tragic icon tied not to a rock, but to the bar in the Queen Vic having her liver pecked at by Shirley but best of all you could have Bobby Beale but transcending time and reality by being a Quantum Leap-esque time traveller going back in time.
